Two international fishing industry groups are urging for tuna catch limits to prevent overfishing.
A recent reduction in bluefin tuna quotas is expected to impact Japan's imports.
Calls for a moratorium on large tuna vessels aim to protect dwindling stocks.
The ongoing meeting in Kobe seeks to establish a global action plan for tuna conservation.
Environmentalists stress the urgent need for sustainable fisheries management.
Efforts include requiring origin certificates for all caught tuna and implementing a tracking system.
The conference unites global bodies to address the decline in valuable tuna populations, emphasizing the importance of cooperation and data sharing.
